# System Diagram

This document describes the high-level architecture of PulseWall and how its components interact.

---

## System Overview

PulseWall is an always-on, wall-powered device built around a Raspberry Pi Pico W and an e-ink display. User interaction is handled using physical rotary knobs.

---

## Components

- Raspberry Pi Pico W  
- SPI e-ink display  
- Two rotary encoders with push buttons  
- USB wall power supply  

---

## Data and Control Flow

```text
Wall Power (USB 5V)
        ↓
Raspberry Pi Pico W
        ↓
E-Ink Display (SPI)
